The paper deals with the study of linear codes in a group algebra, which involves algebraic structures and properties. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with coding theory and its applications. The paper also involves the study of finite abelian groups, which falls under the category of cs.GT (Discrete Mathematics). The study of codes and their properties also involves combinatorial aspects, which falls under the category of cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the study of algebraic structures and properties, which falls under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
